.SH NAME
__drm_atomic_helper_crtc_state_reset \- reset the CRTC state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" __drm_atomic_helper_crtc_state_reset
.BI "(struct drm_crtc_state *crtc_state "  ","
.BI "struct drm_crtc *crtc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "crtc_state" 12
atomic CRTC state, must not be NULL
.IP "crtc" 12
CRTC object, must not be NULL
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Initializes the newly allocated \fIcrtc_state\fP with default
values. This is useful for drivers that subclass the CRTC state.
